"{\"uid\": \"theguardian.com-media-commentisfree-article-2024-jul-26-channel-nine-journalist-strike-olympics-scott-cam-the-block-ntwnfb\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Age reporter questions expense of flying TV personality to Europe while up to 90 staff are cut from newsrooms.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 110, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Plus: Murdoch's real-life succession drama  The presence of the Nine TV personality Scott Cam in Paris to promote The Block was the final provocation for print journalists contemplating strike action on the eve of the Paris Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 111, \"to\": 349, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 117, \"end\": 124, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rupert_Murdoch\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.633810714763508e-41, \"text\": \"Murdoch\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rupert_Murdoch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rupert_Murdoch\"}, {\"begin\": 195, \"end\": 204, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scott_Cam\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Scott Cam\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scott_Cam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scott_Cam\"}, {\"begin\": 208, \"end\": 213, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.818332656986828e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"How many jobs at Nine publishing could have been saved if a TV personality with nothing to do with the Olympics was not going to bed right now in luxury hotels in Paris?\\\"\", \"from\": 351, \"to\": 522, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 515, \"end\": 520, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.818332656986828e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"the Age reporter Broede Carmody told ABC Radio ahead of journalists striking for five days.\", \"from\": 523, \"to\": 614, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 560, \"end\": 569, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Broadcasting_Corporation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.1100830963653575e-15, \"text\": \"ABC Radio\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Broadcasting_Corporation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Broadcasting_Corporation\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There was always going to be a culture clash between Channel Nine and the print mastheads once owned by Fairfax.\", \"from\": 616, \"to\": 728, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 669, \"end\": 681, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nine_Network\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9551763733516727e-47, \"text\": \"Channel Nine\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nine_Network\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nine_Network\"}, {\"begin\": 720, \"end\": 727, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fairfax_Media\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6506385293060443e-55, \"text\": \"Fairfax\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fairfax_Media\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fairfax_Media\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics has been the spark for the biggest fallout sinceNine merged withFairfax in 2018.\", \"from\": 729, \"to\": 822, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Commercial TV networks have traditionally used the Olympics as a platform to promote upcoming shows and the 20th season of The Block, a major success for the network, is no exception.\", \"from\": 824, \"to\": 1007, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But for journalists facing theloss of 90 jobsthe expenditure on TV stars in Paris seemed unreasonable.\", \"from\": 1008, \"to\": 1110, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1084, \"end\": 1089, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.818332656986828e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It did not help that Nine's chief executive, Mike Sneesby, took partin the torch relayhours after the strike was announced.\", \"from\": 1112, \"to\": 1235, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Theanger in newsroomsat the Age, the Sydney Morning Herald, the Australian Financial Review, Brisbane Times and WAtoday has been described as \\\"white hot\\\" after several months of tense enterprise bargaining negotiations were interrupted by news of a substantial cut to editorial resources.\", \"from\": 1237, \"to\": 1525, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1301, \"end\": 1328, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Financial_Review\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Australian Financial Review\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Financial_Review\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Financial_Review\"}, {\"begin\": 1330, \"end\": 1344, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brisbane_Times\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Brisbane Times\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brisbane_Times\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brisbane_Times\"}, {\"begin\": 1349, \"end\": 1356, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WAtoday\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"WAtoday\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WAtoday\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WAtoday\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nothing that Nine's managing director of publishing, Tory Maguire, offered at tense crisis meetings in Melbourne and Sydney on Thursday was enough to call off the strike.\", \"from\": 1527, \"to\": 1697, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1580, \"end\": 1584, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tory\", \"score\": 0.9999999995297912, \"rank\": 4.656886852750103e-10, \"text\": \"Tory\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tory\"}, {\"begin\": 1585, \"end\": 1592, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Maguire\", \"score\": 0.9999999996189217, \"rank\": 3.813962685972802e-10, \"text\": \"Maguire\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Maguire\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Maguire\"}, {\"begin\": 1630, \"end\": 1639, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.0067734087596956e-19, \"text\": \"Melbourne\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne\"}, {\"begin\": 1644, \"end\": 1650, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.684282931748851e-23, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An improved pay offer was rejected.\", \"from\": 1698, \"to\": 1733, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's just not good enough,\\\" Carmody said.\", \"from\": 1735, \"to\": 1777, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We are struggling during this cost-of-living crisis, and we can not take a real wage cut.\", \"from\": 1778, \"to\": 1868, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And at the same time as we were seeking greater protections so that AI could not take our jobs \\u2026 the company announced up to 90 jobs [cut] at our newsrooms.\", \"from\": 1869, \"to\": 2025, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1937, \"end\": 1939, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.307465691681788e-14, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's an awful, awful situation.\\\"\", \"from\": 2026, \"to\": 2058, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Perhaps feeling the pain of the stop-work the most will be the 20-odd journalists, including the Age chief reporter, Chip Le Grand, and the AFR business reporter Zoe Samios, who travelled to Paris to cover the Olympic Games, described by Carmody as \\\"the work trip of a lifetime\\\".\", \"from\": 2060, \"to\": 2339, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2177, \"end\": 2190, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chip_Le_Grand\", \"score\": 0.999999999990905, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chip Le Grand\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chip_Le_Grand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chip_Le_Grand\"}, {\"begin\": 2200, \"end\": 2203, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Financial_Review\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.687631732045886e-73, \"text\": \"AFR\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Financial_Review\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Financial_Review\"}, {\"begin\": 2222, \"end\": 2225, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zoe_Slater\", \"score\": 0.9999902947272704, \"rank\": 9.678771207677183e-06, \"text\": \"Zoe\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zoe_Slater\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zoe_Slater\"}, {\"begin\": 2251, \"end\": 2256, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.818332656986828e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Unlike foreign correspondents, such as the Europe correspondent, Rob Harris, they are not exempt from strike action and will have to take part in the strike as much as it hurts.\", \"from\": 2341, \"to\": 2518, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2406, \"end\": 2416, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamiroquai\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.040903441600537e-37, \"text\": \"Rob Harris\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q215380\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamiroquai\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamiroquai\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Editorial workers at Nine Publishing mastheads will be on strike from 11am AEST tomorrow.We want a pay rise in line with CPI, a commitment to workplace diversity, safeguards around AI and a fair deal for freelancers.#MEAAmedia#DontTorchJournalismpic.twitter.com/LwP3k3FmS8  Sources say the SMH editor, Bevan Shields, got up at the staff meeting to urge staff to consider the wellbeing of those over in Paris.\", \"from\": 2520, \"to\": 2928, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2541, \"end\": 2556, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nine_Entertainment\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nine Publishing\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nine_Entertainment\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nine_Entertainment\"}, {\"begin\": 2701, \"end\": 2703, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.307465691681788e-14, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}, {\"begin\": 2922, \"end\": 2927, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.818332656986828e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One staffer said that was \\\"emotional blackmail\\\", which brought cheers from the crowd.\", \"from\": 2929, \"to\": 3014, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sign up for Guardian Australia's free morning and afternoon email newsletters for your daily news roundup  Sneesby told staff on Friday morning he was \\\"profoundly disappointed\\\" by the decision to strike.\", \"from\": 3016, \"to\": 3219, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3028, \"end\": 3046, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guardian_Australia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Guardian Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guardian_Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guardian_Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Regrettably, the union action comes on the eve of one of the biggest news events on the planet, the Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 3221, \"to\": 3337, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We have invested significantly to bring unrivalled coverage of the 2024 Games to our valued audiences through Nine's world-leading journalism,\\\" Sneesby said in a note to staff seen by Weekly Beast.\", \"from\": 3338, \"to\": 3535, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3448, \"end\": 3452, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nine_Network\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.545230248592403e-33, \"text\": \"Nine\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nine_Network\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nine_Network\"}, {\"begin\": 3529, \"end\": 3534, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beauty_and_the_Beast\", \"score\": 0.9999999999918145, \"rank\": 8.528715505617009e-12, \"text\": \"Beast\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beauty_and_the_Beast\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beauty_and_the_Beast\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sneesby was adamant the strike would not affect the coverage and Nine would continue to \\\"seamlessly deliver the best coverage for our audiences\\\".\", \"from\": 3537, \"to\": 3682, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"More details emerged this week on where the cuts would fall: 10 to 15 staff on the Age and the Sydney Morning Herald would go; six to eight from the national team of federal politics, business, world and environmental journalists.\", \"from\": 3684, \"to\": 3914, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Would love to be covering my first Olympics.But 70-90 redundancies from a profitable section of the business, no hint of exec bonuses being given up, laughably stingy EBA talks and Scott Cam being put up in a five-star Paris hotel?We have got a few things to sort out first.https://t.co/pgvrobBErH  When staff argued for a higher pay offer, Maguire reportedly said if the company went any higher they would have to cut even more staff.\", \"from\": 3916, \"to\": 4351, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4083, \"end\": 4086, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Banking_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999972985833774, \"rank\": 2.6998179920349236e-06, \"text\": \"EBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Banking_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Banking_Authority\"}, {\"begin\": 4097, \"end\": 4106, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scott_Cam\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Scott Cam\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scott_Cam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scott_Cam\"}, {\"begin\": 4135, \"end\": 4140, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.818332656986828e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The mood is not much better at rival media company News Corp Australia, which celebrated the 60th anniversary of The Australian at the same time as the New York Times published a bombshell report that Rupert Murdoch is ina secret legal battlepitching the ageing mogul and his heir apparent, Lachlan Murdoch, against three of his other children.\", \"from\": 4353, \"to\": 4697, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4404, \"end\": 4423, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/News_Corp_Australia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"News Corp Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/News_Corp_Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/News_Corp_Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 4466, \"end\": 4480, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Australian\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2861116616616366e-67, \"text\": \"The Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Australian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Australian\"}, {\"begin\": 4505, \"end\": 4513, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.262525349447041e-13, \"text\": \"New York\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}, {\"begin\": 4554, \"end\": 4568, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rupert_Murdoch\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rupert Murdoch\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rupert_Murdoch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rupert_Murdoch\"}, {\"begin\": 4644, \"end\": 4659, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lachlan_Murdoch\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1385197713888074e-46, \"text\": \"Lachlan Murdoch\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lachlan_Murdoch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lachlan_Murdoch\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The story was taken so seriously by the Sky News Australia host Andrew Bolt thathe threatened to quitif James Murdoch takes over News Corp.  How would we cope?pic.twitter.com/AFGLDcN1dE  \\\"James could sack me if he did take over, but he would not need to.\", \"from\": 4699, \"to\": 4953, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4739, \"end\": 4757, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_News_Australia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sky News Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_News_Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_News_Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 4763, \"end\": 4774, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Bolt\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Andrew Bolt\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Bolt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Bolt\"}, {\"begin\": 4803, \"end\": 4816, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Murdoch\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.0453274513177143e-56, \"text\": \"James Murdoch\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Murdoch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Murdoch\"}, {\"begin\": 4887, \"end\": 4892, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_VI_and_I\", \"score\": 0.9999501490031031, \"rank\": 4.984933091262158e-05, \"text\": \"James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_VI_and_I\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_VI_and_I\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I would not be the only one who would not work for him,\\\" Bolt said.\", \"from\": 4954, \"to\": 5021, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's a values thing.\", \"from\": 5023, \"to\": 5044, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A freedom thing.\", \"from\": 5045, \"to\": 5061, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I do not know if he gets that.\", \"from\": 5062, \"to\": 5092, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sign up toMorning Mail  Our Australian morning briefing breaks down the key stories of the day, telling you what's happening and why it matters  after newsletter promotion  \\\"I have not been asked to say this.\", \"from\": 5094, \"to\": 5302, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I have not even talked to Lachlan for a couple of years.\", \"from\": 5303, \"to\": 5359, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I did not ask for permission to say this.\\\"\", \"from\": 5360, \"to\": 5402, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the absence ofRupert Murdoch, the chosen son Lachlan hosted the gala dinner at the Australian Museum on Thursday night.\", \"from\": 5404, \"to\": 5526, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5428, \"end\": 5435, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rupert_Murdoch\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.633810714763508e-41, \"text\": \"Murdoch\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rupert_Murdoch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rupert_Murdoch\"}, {\"begin\": 5452, \"end\": 5459, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lachlan_Murdoch\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.483780531221992e-14, \"text\": \"Lachlan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lachlan_Murdoch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lachlan_Murdoch\"}, {\"begin\": 5490, \"end\": 5507, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Museum\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Australian Museum\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q33506\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Museum\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Museum\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sitting at the top table with the media mogul was the prime minister, Anthony Albanese, and Coalition leader, Peter Dutton.\", \"from\": 5527, \"to\": 5650, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5597, \"end\": 5613, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anthony_Albanese\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anthony Albanese\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anthony_Albanese\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anthony_Albanese\"}, {\"begin\": 5637, \"end\": 5649, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peter_Dutton\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Peter Dutton\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peter_Dutton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peter_Dutton\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"For 60 years we have spoken fearlessly, and will continue to do so,\\\" Lachlan told the crowd.\", \"from\": 5652, \"to\": 5745, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"For 60 years we have criticised and praised, and brought independent thinking and ideas to our readers and into our communities.\\\"\", \"from\": 5747, \"to\": 5877, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In his speech he criticised social media platforms like Elon Musk's X as \\\"very dangerous\\\".\", \"from\": 5879, \"to\": 5969, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5935, \"end\": 5944, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elon_Musk\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Elon Musk\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elon_Musk\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elon_Musk\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"And this is why journalism, real journalism with real journalists, is so important,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 5971, \"to\": 6065, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Journalists first and foremost report the news, accurately and without bias.\", \"from\": 6067, \"to\": 6144, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We report the facts.\", \"from\": 6145, \"to\": 6165, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We ask questions.\", \"from\": 6166, \"to\": 6183, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We seek the truth.\\\"\", \"from\": 6184, \"to\": 6203, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Albanesereportedly saidRupert Murdoch \\\"willed into being a newspaper\\\" in an \\\"act of audacity, of \\u00adambition and of optimism that \\u00adreflects the qualities and the story of our great nation\\\".\", \"from\": 6205, \"to\": 6392, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6235, \"end\": 6242, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rupert_Murdoch\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.633810714763508e-41, \"text\": \"Murdoch\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rupert_Murdoch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rupert_Murdoch\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Among the 250 guests were the former prime ministers John Howard and Tony Abbott, New South Wales premier Chris Minns, \\u00adthe governor general, Samantha Mostyn, and Senator Jacinta Nampijinpa Price.\", \"from\": 6394, \"to\": 6590, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6447, \"end\": 6458, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Howard\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.26157760385592e-35, \"text\": \"John Howard\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Howard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Howard\"}, {\"begin\": 6463, \"end\": 6474, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Abbott\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4258779073582323e-72, \"text\": \"Tony Abbott\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Abbott\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Abbott\"}, {\"begin\": 6500, \"end\": 6511, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Minns\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chris Minns\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q2156