.org/resource/Australian_Broadcasting_Corporation\"}, {\"begin\": 6854, \"end\": 6867, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Uhlmann\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chris Uhlmann\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Uhlmann\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Uhlmann\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We need to reject shallow nationalism and redeem the idea of patriotism,\\\" Uhlmann said.\", \"from\": 6970, \"to\": 7058, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With all eyes on the 60th anniversary and Lachlan in town, News Corp tried to keep a lid on thepainful newsabout the rolling redundancies at the Murdoch empire in an effort to save $65m.\", \"from\": 7060, \"to\": 7246, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7102, \"end\": 7109, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lachlan_Murdoch\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.483780531221992e-14, \"text\": \"Lachlan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lachlan_Murdoch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lachlan_Murdoch\"}, {\"begin\": 7119, \"end\": 7128, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/News_Corp_Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999999812889657, \"rank\": 1.8711084818957552e-08, \"text\": \"News Corp\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/News_Corp_Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/News_Corp_Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 7205, \"end\": 7212, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rupert_Murdoch\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.633810714763508e-41, \"text\": \"Murdoch\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rupert_Murdoch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rupert_Murdoch\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some of the most experienced News journalists were quietly culled and there were farewells held at the Shakespeare hotel in Surry Hills this week and many a farewell card signed.\", \"from\": 7248, \"to\": 7426, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7351, \"end\": 7362, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Shakespeare\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7019895548084161e-18, \"text\": \"Shakespeare\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Shakespeare\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Shakespeare\"}, {\"begin\": 7372, \"end\": 7383, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Results_of_the_1904_New_South_Wales_state_election\", \"score\": 0.60393036888295, \"rank\": 0.6558200274800516, \"text\": \"Surry Hills\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Results_of_the_1904_New_South_Wales_state_election\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Results_of_the_1904_New_South_Wales_state_election\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is the final day of daily journalism for the great Sue Dunlevy, our top medical/health policy reporter.\", \"from\": 7428, \"to\": 7536, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7484, \"end\": 7487, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sue_Sylvester\", \"score\": 0.9994979332895024, \"rank\": 0.0005023177951251423, \"text\": \"Sue\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sue_Sylvester\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sue_Sylvester\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A big loss for News Corp readers.pic.twitter.com/rPZ8cwnGv5  Decades of experience was let go when the much-admired veteran national health reporter, Sue Dunlevy, was made redundant, among dozens of others.\", \"from\": 7537, \"to\": 7743, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7687, \"end\": 7690, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sue_Sylvester\", \"score\": 0.9994979332895024, \"rank\": 0.0005023177951251423, \"text\": \"Sue\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sue_Sylvester\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sue_Sylvester\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her departure will be a big loss to the reporting of health policy in this country.\", \"from\": 7744, \"to\": 7827, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A straight shooter, Dunlevy has risen above politics and allowed her reporting to do the talking in a 36-year career at News Corp.\", \"from\": 7829, \"to\": 7959, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7949, \"end\": 7958, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/News_Corp_Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999999812889657, \"rank\": 1.8711084818957552e-08, \"text\": \"News Corp\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/News_Corp_Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/News_Corp_Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This story was amended on 26 July 2024 to accurately reflect what Bevan Shields said at the staff meeting.\", \"from\": 7961, \"to\": 8067, \"entities\": []}]}"